x-kaytu-explanation:
The `audit_log_enabled` control in Azure is used to enable auditing on MySQL servers. Auditing is a security measure that records all the events occurring on your MySQL server. This includes login attempts, queries executed, and changes in database structure. It helps you monitor the server, detect suspicious activities, and comply with regulatory standards.

Enabling `audit_log_enabled` control will help to track these events and find out what happened, when it happened, and who made the change.

Here is how you can enable it in the Azure Policy JSON format:

```json
{
  "properties": {
    "displayName": "Enable audit log on MySQL servers",
    "policyType": "BuiltIn",
    "mode": "Indexed",
    "description": "This policy enables the audit log on MySQL servers.",
    "metadata": {
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "category": "SQL"
    },
    "parameters": {},
    "policyRule": {
      "if": {
        "allOf": [
          {
            "field": "type",
            "equals": "Microsoft.DBforMySQL/servers"
          },
          {
            "field": "Microsoft.DBforMySQL/servers/auditingSettings[*].state",
            "notEquals": "Enabled"
          }
        ]
      },
      "then": {
        "effect": "DeployIfNotExists",
        "details": {
          "type": "Microsoft.DBforMySQL/servers/auditingSettings",
          "existenceCondition": {
            "field": "Microsoft.DBforMySQL/servers/auditingSettings[*].state",
            "equals": "Enabled"
          },
          "roleDefinitionIds": [
            "/providers/microsoft.authorization/roleDefinitions/XXXX"
          ],
          "deployment": {
            "properties": {
              "parameters": {
                "auditingSettingsName": {
                  "value": "default"
                },
                "state": {
                  "value": "Enabled"
                }
              },
              "template": {
                "$schema": "http://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2015-01-01/deploymentTemplate.json#",
                "contentVersion": "1.0.0.0",
                "resources": [
                  {
                    "type": "Microsoft.DBforMySQL/servers/auditingSettings",
                    "apiVersion": "2017-12-01",
                    "name": "[concat(parameters('auditingSettingsName'))]",
                    "properties": {
                      "state": "[parameters('state')]"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
This policy checks if auditing is enabled on all MySQL servers (`Microsoft.DBforMySQL/servers`) and if not it deploys the necessary resources to enable it. As the effect is `DeployIfNotExists`, it will only perform the action if auditing is disabled.
